            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make the coconut-pecan filling",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Combine the evaporated milk, sugar, beaten egg yolks, and butter in a saucepan. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, for 12 to 15 minutes until the mixture thickens and turns a light amber-caramel colour. Remove from heat and stir in the vanilla, coconut, and pecans. The filling will thicken further as it cools; allow it to reach room temperature before using.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Bake the cake layers",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Preheat the oven to 175°C conventional. Grease and line three 23 cm round tins. Whisk together the dry ingredients. In a separate bowl, whisk the eggs, buttermilk, oil, and vanilla. Combine wet and dry ingredients, then add the hot water in a steady stream and stir until smooth, the batter will be thin. Divide between the tins and bake for 30 to 35 minutes until a skewer comes out clean. Cool in the tins for 15 minutes, then on racks.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Assemble",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Place the first sponge layer on a plate. Spread one third of the cooled filling over the top, spreading to within 1 cm of the edge. Add the second layer and repeat, then place the third layer on top and finish with the remaining filling. The sides of this cake are traditionally left unfrosted; the coconut-pecan filling is the only topping required.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
